Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
add_gui_shape(25.10)                                      add_gui_shape(25.10)

Name
       add_gui_shape

Syntax
       add_gui_shape

       [-help]

       [-layer <layerName>]

       [-name <guiShapeName>]

       [-width <width>]

       {-rect  {x1 y1 x2 y2} | -line {x1 y1 x2 y2 ...} | -polygon {x1 y1 x2 y2
       ...}}

       [-line {x1 y1 x2 y2 ...} [-arrow ] ]

       Adds a shape to the default or specified custom layer. You can use  the
       add_gui_shape command at any point in the design flow. The shapes added
       by  the  command  annotate comment shapes and do not show up in the DEF
       output.

       Note: In OpenAccess flows, the shapes added with the add_gui_shape com-
       mand are stored in the OpenAccess cellview.  However,  the  shapes  are
       stored  in  a  private structure that is accessible only to Innovus. To
       create shapes that are visible in Virtuoso as well, use  the  add_shape
       command instead.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each add_gui_shape parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man add_gui_shape

       -arrow Draws an arrow in the middle of the line segment to indicate the
              start  to  end  direction.  This parameter can only be used with
              -line.

       -layer <layerName>
              Specifies the GUI layer name to use or create for the shape.  If
              the specified layer does not exist, it is created automatically.

              If  a  layer  is not specified, the tool automatically creates a
              layer with the name defaultLayer and adds the shape to it.

       -line {<x1 y1 x2 y2 ...>}
              Creates a line, with x1 y1 x2 y2 ... specifying the  coordinates
              for the line segments. The values are specified in microns.

       -name <guiShapeName>
              Specifies the name of the GUI shape.

       -polygon {<x1 y1 x2 y2> ...}
              Creates a polygon shape, with x1 y1 x2 y2 ... specifying the co-
              ordinates  for the polygon segments. The values are specified in
              microns.

       -rect {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}
              Specifies the coordinates  of  the  lower-left  and  upper-right
              points of the rectangle. The values are specified in microns.

       -width <width>
              Specifies  the  width of the shape border in pixels. The minimum
              (default) value is 1 and the maximum is  7.

Examples
              *

                The following command adds a triangular shape in layer 1:

                add_gui_shape -layer 1 -polygon {95.841 -645  96.592  -644.147
                96.926 -644.777}

              *

                The following command adds a line shape with two segments:

                add_gui_shape  -layer  1  -line  {95.841  -645 96.592 -644.147
                96.926 -644.777}

              * The following command adds a line shape with two segments  and
                direction arrows:

                add_gui_shape  -layer  1  -line  {95.841  -645 96.592 -644.147
                96.926 -644.777} -arrow

              *

                The following command adds a line shape of 3-pixel width:

                add_gui_shape -layer 1  -line  {95.841  -645  96.592  -644.147
                96.926 -644.777} -width 3

